data.text:
"AUNTIE MAME"

1958

Director: MORTON DaCOSTA

ROSALIND RUSSELL, FOREST TUCKER, PEGGY CASS

All seats $8.00

35MM PRESENTATION

"Life is a banquet, and most poor suckers are starving to death!" So says the high-flying Auntie Mame, whose lavish parties never seem to end. But when her nephew is suddenly orphaned, and the Depression wipes out her savings, is our heroine going stop feasting at life's banquet? Not in a million years! Rosalind Russell never shined so bright as she did in the role that defined her career.

35mm print courtesy Warner Bros.

Advance tickets are available.
